node.text: parenting: a blessing and a curse. i always took pride in how easy it was for us to keep the romance alive; late nights drinking wine, deep conversations about life, foot massages… until this little one came along. it seems like there’s no time for us any more. every photo on his page is just him… or him and the baby. i know that’s a small thing but, sometimes it hurts. which one of us gets up when she’s crying in the middle of the night? who does it more often? who’s turn is it to change the diaper? am i still loved as much as i was before? have we started to resent each other or are we just tired and on edge because of all the extra work it takes to raise a child? i know we’ll get through this, i just had to vent.
